    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO SERIES - INSTALL - COUNTERSHAFT BEARINGS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1301704" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="5">
        <title>COUNTERSHAFT BEARINGS</title>
        <para>The front bearing inner race must be pressed on the countershaft front.</para>
        <para>The flanged-end driver must cover the bearing outer race for proper installation.</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Move the countershaft to the rear and support the countershaft to center the shaft in the
                rear case bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017k2">Figure 202</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017k2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017k2" filename="../figg13/G13017k2.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 202. Center The Shaft In Rear Case Bore</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a flanged-end driver to start the front bearing in the case bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017k3">Figure 203</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017k3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017k3" filename="../figg13/G13017k3.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 203. Front Bearing In Case Bore</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a screwdriver inserted in the countershaft bolt hole to help center the countershaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017k4">Figure 204</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017k4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017k4" filename="../figg13/G13017k4.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 204. Countershaft Forward Into Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Move the countershaft forward into the bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017k4">Figure 204</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a flanged-end bearing driver and maul to completely seat the front bearing in the case
                bore.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">On the countershaft front, position the retainer plate with roll pin in hole at shaft end (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017k4">Figure 204</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Secure with a bolt, tightening to 90 to 120 ft-lbs. (122 to 163 N&#8226;m) of torque.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the countershaft rear support fixture.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the larger I.D. lead chamfer to the shaft front, use a flanged-end bearing driver and
                install the rear bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017k5">Figure 205</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017k5" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017k5" filename="../figg13/G13017k5.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 205. Install Rear Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the rear snap ring in the countershaft rear groove (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017k6">Figure 206</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017k6" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017k6" filename="../figg13/G13017k6.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 206. Snap Ring In Countershaft Groove</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
